#: ../../tips_and_tricks/shooting_tips/shooting_with_your_DSLR.rst:53
msgid ""
"Directly related to the previous point about lenses. Shooting with an open "
"aperture works well as long as it is dark. In bright sunlight it will fail "
"because there is too much light falling on the sensor. Furthermore you are "
"forced to use a high shutter speed which makes movements look jerky; Most of "
"the time you will want to have some kind of motion blur because it looks "
"more natural to our eyes."
msgstr ""
"Neposredno povezano s prejšnjo točko o objektivih. Snemanje z odprto "
"zaslonko deluje dobro, dokler je temno. Pri svetli sončni svetlobi bo "
"odpovedalo, ker na senzor pada preveč svetlobe. Poleg tega ste prisiljeni "
"uporabiti visoko hitrost zaklopa, zaradi česar so gibi videti trzajoče; "
"večino časa boste želeli imeti nekakšno zabrisanost gibanja, ker je videti "
"bolj naravno za naše oči."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/shooting_tips/shooting_with_your_DSLR.rst:55
msgid ""
"If you ever tried to follow a bird or another animal with your eyes in dawn, "
"you will know that our eyes do support motion blur."
msgstr ""
"Če ste kdaj poskušali slediti ptici ali drugi živali z očmi ob zori, boste "
"vedeli, da naše oči podpirajo zabrisanost gibanja."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/shooting_tips/shooting_with_your_DSLR.rst:57
msgid ""
"So the trick is to remove some light with a filter called Neutral Density "
"Filter."
msgstr ""
"Torej je trik, da odstranite nekaj svetlobe s filtrom, imenovanim filter "
"nevtralne gostote."

