#: ../../tips_and_tricks/shooting_tips/shooting_with_your_DSLR.rst:74
msgid ""
"The same as for shooting stills. Really? Not quite. As written above you "
"will usually want to have the shutter speed lower than for photography in "
"order to get motion blur — around 1/50 s. (This is just a rule of thumb, as "
"all rules in video are - made to be broken.)"
msgstr ""
"Tako kot pri slikanju fotografij. Res? Ne povsem. Kot je zapisano zgoraj, "
"boste običajno želeli, da je hitrost zaklopa nižja kot za fotografiranje, da "
"bi dobili zabrisanost gibanja – okoli 1/50 s (to je samo subjektivna ocena, "
"kot vse glede videa; narejena, da jo kršimo)."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/shooting_tips/shooting_with_your_DSLR.rst:76
msgid ""
"Also, some additional problems may arise due to the sensor being read out "
"line-wise. One I would like to mention are Rolling Shutter effects. Longer "
"exposure can, but need not, prevent such problems. It does if you are "
"shooting with fluorescent lamps. Shooting at high shutter speed shows wave "
"patterns from top to bottom of the screen, lowering it hides them if you hit "
"the correct shutter speed."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega se lahko pojavijo nekatere dodatne težave zaradi branja tipala v "
"vrsticah. Rad bi omenil učinke vrtečega zaklopa (angl. rolling shutter). "
"Daljša izpostavljenost lahko, vendar ne vedno, prepreči takšne težave. Če "
"snemate s fluorescenčnimi lučmi. Snemanje z visoko hitrostjo zaklopa "
"prikazuje valovite vzorce od vrha do dna zaslona, znižanje jih skrije, če "
"zadenete pravo hitrost zaklopa."

